<span id="freeTextContainer1908929322611511849">Stanley Kubrick was going to turn this book into a movie called The Aryan Papers. It would have made a great movie. It still could. <br/><br/>It avoids many Holocaust cliches. Instead of lingering on gratuitous grief and murder, it’s more about how war changes people and empties them.<br/><br/>It starts slow, gets better as it goes along, and eases into a satisfying conclusion just as you’ve had your fill. </span>

