              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3158882794219884447">It moves a little slow, but it is a short, concise book. It is supposedly semi-autobiographical. A Jewish boy and his aunt escape the Warsaw ghetto by passing themselves off as Catholics. Over the years, in order to survive, the lies build. It is narrated by the boy as a grown man, long after the war, still living the lie. Very well written.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


