<div id="review_4060305683" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4060305683" />
    <a title="Doxieluv" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6997713-doxieluv"><img alt="Doxieluv" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4060305683?book_show_action=true">Jun 15, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Doxieluv" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Doxieluv" href="/user/show/6997713-doxieluv">Doxieluv</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/10870546-wartime-lies">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4060305683" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2242965644575710955">Sadly, this book could not hold my interest. I plodded thru it and in the end, think my dislike was the premise behind the story. It was trying to make the case that all the lying done to save An Aunt and her 9yo nephew from the Nazis was detrimental to their mental health. I would think that if a lie saves my life it is necessary and no second-guessing should be necessary. Perhaps because it is largely from the child&apos;s POV maybe he saw if that much differently. Just MHO.</span>
  <span id="freeText2242965644575710955" style="display:none">Sadly, this book could not hold my interest. I plodded thru it and in the end, think my dislike was the premise behind the story. It was trying to make the case that all the lying done to save An Aunt and her 9yo nephew from the Nazis was detrimental to their mental health. I would think that if a lie saves my life it is necessary and no second-guessing should be necessary. Perhaps because it is largely from the child's POV maybe he saw if that much differently. Just MHO.</span>
