    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1137353958" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1137353958" />
    <a title="Arvinder S." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17990381-arvinder-s"><img alt="Arvinder S." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1607470278p2/17990381.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1137353958?book_show_action=true">Dec 21, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Arvinder S." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Arvinder S." href="/user/show/17990381-arvinder-s">Arvinder S.</a>
      </span>

          added it




        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer1137353958&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1137353958" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18008166550373720059"><br/>+ The first chapter does a good job of building a sense of family and community through the various examples of everyone coming together to help out the main character and the examples and details of each of the relationships the main character had with other characters. This continues throughout the novel as relationships between the characters, both good and bad, are developed really well even without lots of dialogue. <br/><br/>+ The symbology of the beds was nice. They kept getting lower and lower as </span>
  <span id="freeText18008166550373720059" style="display:none"><br />+ The first chapter does a good job of building a sense of family and community through the various examples of everyone coming together to help out the main character and the examples and details of each of the relationships the main character had with other characters. This continues throughout the novel as relationships between the characters, both good and bad, are developed really well even without lots of dialogue. <br /><br />+ The symbology of the beds was nice. They kept getting lower and lower as their despair pushed them farther and farther into the ground, and by the time that despair was lifted, they were pushed away from who they were before the despair began. <br /><br />+Poses an interesting perspective on a well-documented and explored era. The aspect of Jews exploiting each other along with the betrayal of self in order to survive are both angles on a subject that are relatively fresh and breath-taking. <br /><br />-Some the character’s importance wasn’t really honed in due to the limited nature of the story being told through Maciel’s perspective. Case and point is Reinherd; his death did not really hit me as hard as the grandmother’s, even though she was an asshole. This further bled into the later despair not really feeling as if it was all that dire, though I think this was something the author was probably going for, seeing as how the tone of this text towards that dark time was more critical of the people behind the atrocities than the actual atrocities themselves. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="18008166550373720059" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


