    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1023613138" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1023613138" />
    <a title="Erin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3112139-erin"><img alt="Erin" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1023613138?book_show_action=true">Aug 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Erin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Erin" href="/user/show/3112139-erin">Erin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1023613138" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7099028204437099269">Wartime lines portrayed a seemingly fictional account of a young Jewish boy in Poland, and his experiences during WWII under the care of his aunt. With the assistance of lies, false papers with fake identities, and the quick, cunning nature of his aunt, the two were able to survive the war without capture or death. The book is narrated from the young boy&apos;s point of view and provides a unique viewpoint into the drastic measures individuals would take survive during the war. It was a slight surpri</span>
  <span id="freeText7099028204437099269" style="display:none">Wartime lines portrayed a seemingly fictional account of a young Jewish boy in Poland, and his experiences during WWII under the care of his aunt. With the assistance of lies, false papers with fake identities, and the quick, cunning nature of his aunt, the two were able to survive the war without capture or death. The book is narrated from the young boy's point of view and provides a unique viewpoint into the drastic measures individuals would take survive during the war. It was a slight surprise, when, reading the afterward, the author confesses that the story was based in part in his own experiences during the war. All in all, an interesting read. But as I've written before, it's hard to say you greatly enjoyed a book that is about characters involved in or escaping the Holocaust. But if one is looking for a different perspective, it is a book I would recommend.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7099028204437099269" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


